SIMPLE: electorate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Electorate
<hw>E*lect"or*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧lectorat</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The territory,
jurisdiction, or dignity of an elector, as in the old German
empire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The whole body of persons in a nation or state who
are entitled to vote in an election, or any distinct class or division
of them.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The middle-class <qex>electorate</qex> of Great Britain.</q>
<rj><qau>M. Arnold.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Electoress</ent>⟦br⟧
